servings: 2
---

Fill and boil your #kettle{}. Halve the @Baby Plum Tomatoes{125}. Zest and halve the @Lemon{½}. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} over medium-high heat. Once hot, add the tomatoes and garlic and cook, stir, until softened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add the @water for the sauce{75%ml} with the @Vegetable Stock Powder{1}(tsp), stirring well to dissolve the stock.

Add the @Creme Fraiche{150%ml}, @Green Pesto{1}(tablespoon) and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, bring to a simmer.

Pour the boiling water to a large #saucepan{} on a high heat with 0.5 tsp @salt{0.5%tsp} and bring back to a boil.

Add the @Fresh Tagliatelle{200%g} to the pan of boiling water and cook for ~{3%minutes}.

Add the @King Prawns{180%g} and @Baby Spinach{100%g} to the sauce and cook, stirring, until the prawns are cooked and the spinach has wilted, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Drain the tagliatelle in a #colander{} then stir through the sauce with half the lemon zest and a squeeze of lemon juice, adding a splash of water if to loosen if it needs it.

Divide between plates. Sprinkle the remaining lemon zest on top. Enjoy!